<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="description" content="LGA Briefing" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>LGA submission to Transport Select Committee inquiry on the ‘Strategic Road Network’</title></head><body><div><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Written evidence from the Local Government Association (SRN 014)</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:center; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><br style="clear:both; mso-break-type:section-break; page-break-before:auto" /><div><ol type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">About the Local Government Association (LGA)</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">1.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Local Government Association (LGA) is the national voice of local government. </span><a name="_GoBack"></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We work with councils to support, promote and improve local government.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We are a politically-led, cross party organisation which works on behalf of councils to ensure local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">government has a strong, credible voice with national government.  We aim to influence and set the political agenda on the issues that matter to councils so they are able to deliver local solutions to national problems.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="2" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Overview</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Strategic Roads Network </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">(SRN) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">should not be considered in isolation from the local roads network or from transport </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">provision </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">as a whole.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> For instance, roads policy should be considered alongside, and integrated with, rail policy.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This reflects an under</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lying principle running through the LGA’s  campaign, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Rewiring Public Services</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">which argues</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> for</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> joined up</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> approach to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> infrastructure investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Route based assessments need to be a genuine coproduction between local authorities and the Highways Agency</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and need to consider all modes of transport and the local road network</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Investment in the SRN needs to be coordinated with the Strategic Economic Plans produced by </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Local Enterprise Partnerships (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">LEPs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> as well as existing City Deal agreements.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">o avoid gridlock on our roads, including the SRN, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">councils need greater influence over local transport provision</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">2.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Department for Transport’s (DfT)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> traffic estimates </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">do not represent guaranteed futures which must be accommodated. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Future traffic levels </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">depend on the policies pursued today.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="3" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Inquiry question: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How will the policies set out in the Government’s “Action for Roads” command paper improve the strategic road network for all road users, whilst also improving the environment?</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="4" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Inquiry question: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How does the Government’s policy for roads link with planning for other transport modes?</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="5" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We have answered these questions togeth</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">er because we believe that the G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment’s policies cannot be expected to deliver an improved SRN, or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">improve the environment, unless investment in the SRN is combined with improvements to local roads and planning for other forms of transport at a local level. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="6" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The need for a comprehensive approach </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">6.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> concerns itself chiefly with the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">SRN. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">owever it recognises that ‘almost every journey starts or ends’ on the 98 per cent of the road network for which councils are responsible. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">6.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The SRN cannot therefore be considered in isolation from the local roads network</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> or </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">local transport as a whole</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (si</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nce</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> traffic on the local network is influenced by the provision of alternative transpor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t).</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">6.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This is true in three ways in particular:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6.3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The tendency of new roads to generate ‘induced traffic’ is a well-established fact and has led previous road building sch</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">emes to fail to deliver anticipated benefits. Indeed as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> points out </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">roads support job creation and unlock new development</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. This is good news when the traffic generated as a result can be accommodated (and when the developments are </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">genuinely new rather than relocated)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">where the intention</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">behind investment in the SRN is to encourage development, the ability of the local roads network to handle more traffic will have to be carefully considered as part of the investment plan. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6.3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Where the aim of increasing SRN capacity is to relieve congestion investment needs to be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">planned in a manner that avoids creating</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> substantial new traffic. Ignoring local transport provision while expanding the capacity of the SRN to meet a 46 per cent tr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">affic increase by 2040 will simply move people more quickly between gridlocked local roads. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6.3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Many of the current journeys on the SRN are relatively short-distance journeys which could be diverted from it by changes to local transport arrangements – either</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> local road improvements or public transport alternatives. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">6.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The tasks above cannot be performed by central government alone but will re</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">quire effective coordination between </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">central and local government.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">6.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In practical</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> terms we think three developments are required:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6.5.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Councils need to be</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> equal partners</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> in devising the route based strategies that will provide the basis of investment in the SRN</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6.5.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">he programme of investment in the SRN needs to be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">combined</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with investment in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> local major schemes via the Local Growth Fund and agreements reached through the City Deal process</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">6.5.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Councils need to be able to manage traffic effectively both through direct traffic management means and indirectly via the provision of alternative means </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of transport.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="7" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Devising Route Based Strategies</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">7.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Government has spoken encouragingly of involving local authorities in devising the route based strategies which are intended to shape the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">programme of investment in the SRN. These discussions are supposed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to be completed in time to feed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> into</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> a Roads Investment Strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to be published by 2015.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">7.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The route-based strategy approach offers an opportunity to make investment in roads more effective and is one the LGA supports. However, it remains to be seen how </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">effectively the Highways Agency will engage with councils on this programme of work. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Local Growth Fund </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">(LGF) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">and the SRN</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The development of the Roads Investment Strategy needs to be </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">combined</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with transport investment through the LGF.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Action for </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Roads</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> refers to the Government’s efforts:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to free up other money that local authoriti</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">es use to fund larger projects…</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">reduce the strings attached to local funding for major schemes</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”, and decentralise “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">decision-making to reduce the number of situations where</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> councils need to get approval from Whitehall before starting work</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">However</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> it is now clear that central control of spending has not been abolished and that</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> instead of the original DfT proposal to allocate money to Local Transport Boards, LEPs will now</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> have to compete for funds through their Strategic Economic Plans. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">At the time of writing it is unclear on what basis these plans will be judged, but it does seem that the timetable for their production means that work on them </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">needs to be completed befor</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e anyone knows the order of priority in the roads programme. We believe that drafting a plan for transport in a LEP area with no knowledge of the timetable for i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mproving the SRN in that area, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">or even knowledge</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> of what measures might be used, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">adds to the co</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mplexity of the task and makes it more likely that the conclusions reached will be open to question. This problem is exacerbated </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">if an effective relationship has not developed between </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the Highways Agency </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and the relevant LEP(s). </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">8.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Officials at the Departme</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nt for Transport and the Department for Business, Innovation and Skills </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">are working hard with local authorities and LEPs to bring clarity to these pro</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">cesses and address these issues. However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">we struggle to see how it will be possible to sensibly align the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> roads programme and local transpo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rt investment plans within the G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment’s timetable. In any case</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> this process is not devolution. If the sums in the LGF were truly devolved</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> councils would be better placed to manage the uncertainty over the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Roads Inves</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tment Strategy</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> because </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">they would not have to commit themselves on other investment according to a centrally-</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">determined political timetable (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">based on the dates of general elections</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.17pt; orphans:0; padding-left:3.83pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Effective Traffic Management</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">9.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">If these investment programmes are to deliver best value they need to be accompanied by effective traffic management at local level and the provision of alternative transport facilities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> including encoura</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">gement for cycling and walking. However, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">councils cu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">rrently lack the tools to do </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">this.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">9.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> is right to recognise </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">need to give local authorities the freedom, the flexibility and the capacity</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">“</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">shape the future of their local transport – especially the roles to be played by roads, by di</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">fferent types of public transport and by cycling</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. To date however</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the current government has not lived up to its initial promises of devolution in transport.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">9.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Councils understand better than anyone that there is no bottomless pit of cash to solve ou</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">r </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">transport (or other) problems</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. If local transport networks are to b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">e improved we need</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> innovate, rather than simply</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> spend more. If we are to get best value from transport investment</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> councils need to be positioned to consider local transport as a whole</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. This would allow them to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">encourage the use of alternative modes where this is effective while increasing capacity to the local road network through intelligent interventions, both to accommodate increased traffic arriving from the SRN and to reduce the i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mpact of local traffic on the SRN. If councils are to take the measures necessary to avoid gridlock in the next two decades they will need:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9.3.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Powers in </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">P</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">art 6 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Traffic Management Act </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">2004 </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to enforce moving traffic offences</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9.3.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Effective leverage to influ</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ence bus and train operating companies to ensure a local transport network that serves the needs of business</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">es</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and communities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">; </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9.3.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Adequate funding to maintain the local road network; and</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 61.2pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-25.2pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9.3.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Meaningful devolution of investment funds</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Inquiry q</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">uestion: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How relia</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">ble is the Government’s forecast for growth in demand for the strategic road network? How should the Government deal with uncertainty in its forecast? </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In answering this question it is important to bear in mind what the Government itself says about these </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">forecast</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">:</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> “</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The NTM Road Traffic Forecasts should not be viewed as what we think will actually happen in the future, or what we want the future to look like. The forecasts are what may happen, based on: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Our current understanding of how people make travel c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hoices</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The expected path of key drivers of travel demand</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Assuming no change in government policy beyond that already announced</span><span style="font-family:'Frutiger 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">”</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In other words</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the forecasts are not a given around which policy must be constructed, but the likely outcome of existing </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">policy. Uncertainty around that outcome merely highlights the opportunity for a different set of outcomes to be achieved by different policies.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The LGA does not advocate a particular national polic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">y. H</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">owever</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the prospect of pursuing a policy of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">‘</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">predict </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and provide</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> along the mid-range estimate of a 46 per cent increase in traffic on the SRN over the next 25 years</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> (as suggested by the Government’s forecast)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> poses the question of  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">w</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">hat will happen to this additional traffic when it leaves the SRN? </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10.4.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Df</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">T’s estimates suggest an increase in traffic outside the SRN of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">23</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-64% leading to an increase in non-SRN congestion of 25-101%. However</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> the real picture will be much worse for councils than this suggests, as that congestion will be concentrated in particu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">lar areas, implying an increase in traffic in main urban centres which they </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">would struggle to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">accommodate.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10.5.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">Action for Roads</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> appears to gloss over this prospect by claiming that: “Strategic roads may be under more pressure than their local counterparts. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Between 2000 and 2012, the last year for which there is confirmed data, motorists drove an extra ten billion miles on strategic roads, while traffic was steady on the rest of the network”.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10.6.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This is </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">misleading since </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">between 2000 and 2007 traffic </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">actually </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">grew on both SRN and local networks</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">. Since then, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">SRN traffic levels have stabilised while traffic on the local roads network has fallen to 2000 levels. In other words when the economy was doing well local traffic was increasing and we suspect that pressure</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> on local roads will increase by more than DfT predicts as the economy recovers.</span><a name="_ftnref4"></a><a href="#_ftn4">[4]</a></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10.7.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">A 46 per cent increase in traffic is not inevitable. Nor is it desirable on an across the board basis. It is clear that road freight transport will be the essential carrier </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">of economic growth in the next quarter of a century and that the car will remain essential for many journeys, especially in rural areas. This makes it all the more important to provide alternative forms of transport where possible</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> so that the essential ca</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">r and lorry journeys are not made impossible or inefficient by congestion. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">10.8.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">This reinforces the points we have made previously about the need for local authorities to be empowered to deliver better transport and free up the local road network.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="11" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Inquiry q</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">u</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">estion: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How can we improve the reliability and efficiency of travel on the strategic road network? What impact will new technology have?</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">11.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We have already set out the reasons why we think a localist</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> approach is necessary to deliver improved reliability and efficiency on the SRN.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">11.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Councils are continuing to invest in, and innovate with, the use of new technology when it comes to their management of the local road network. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Deeper engagement between lo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">cal authorities and the Highways Agency </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">could provide further opportunities for improving and sharing respective expertise and technologies across the SRN and the local network. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="12" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Inquiry question: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">What mechanisms are there for Government to increase inves</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">tment in strategic roads and attract new investors? Are there good examples from other countries that could be applied in the</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">UK? </span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">12.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The LGA has already called for the G</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">overnment to boost investment in infrastructure by re-creating the thriving market in mu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">nicipal bonds which England once had and most other countries still have.</span><a name="_ftnref5"></a><a href="#_ftn5">[5]</a></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">12.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Transport is a prime example of where such measures could help lever in private funding and have a significant impact on the ability of local councils to a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ddress local transport problems, as well as </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">contribute to the solution of national ones as a consequence.</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Inquiry q</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">uestion: </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">How should the Highways Agency be reformed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">to make it “the world’s leading highway operator”? What roles should Government and the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">private sector play to ensure better management of the strategic road network?</span></li></ol><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">13.1.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The LGA believes that the key reform to the Highways Agency</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, which in itself is long overdue,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> must be to ensure that it engages effectively</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> with local authorities. This must ha</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ppen</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> not only </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">when it comes to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> devising route based strategies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">, but also </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> respect to</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> devising and developing the Strategic Economic Plans</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> which</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> LEPs have been asked to deliver as bids for local growth funds. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">13.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">For too long the Highways Agency has been </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">seen</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and has seen itself</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> as an organisation that only deals with the SRN and this has led to that network being treated as something that exists in isolation from local transport networks. In reality</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> strategic routes are at the heart of an area’s transp</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ort picture. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">13.3.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">If the country at large</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> and local areas</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> are to maximise the benefit from our SRN</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> then it is critical that businesses and local leaders are at the heart of decision making for all our strategic routes.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> The Highways Agency must become more </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">holistic in its approach, and consider its impact on housing delivery  and other local services. </span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">October 2013</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; text-align:right; widows:0"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger 45 Light'; font-size:11pt">6</span></p><p style="line-height:13pt; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> More information on the campaign is available on the LGA website: </span><a href="http://www.local.gov.uk/publications/-/journal_content/56/10180/4047947/PUBLICATION"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.local.gov.uk/publications/-/journal_content/56/10180/4047947/PUBLICATION</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">‘Action for R</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">oads</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">’</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> is available at </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/212590/action-for-roads.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/212590/action-for-roads.pdf</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> . This reference is taken from p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">aragraph 2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">1</span></p><h2 style="font-weight:normal; margin:0pt; orphans:0; widows:0"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">DfT </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">Road Transport Forecasts 2013 - </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic">Results from the Department for Transport's National Transport Model </span><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/212474/road-transport-forecasts-2013.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/212474/road-transport-forecasts-2013.pdf</span